{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Marketers trying to reach an increasingly fractured and fickle social media audience are struggling to make ads when one version may not work everywhere....", "abstract": "Advertising column; advertisers are experimenting with silent video ads, skipping catchy jingle and familiar voiceover to take advantage of Facebook's News Feed platform; marketing experts doubt ads will be very effective since most studies indicate consumers recall video ads with sound much more than those without it; trend shows how fragmented audience is forcing advertisers to put aside traditions and explore other means of reaching consumers. ", "section_name": "Business Day", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Sapna", "role": "reported", "lastname": "MAHESHWARI", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}, {"firstname": "Katie", "role": "reported", "lastname": "BENNER", "rank": 2, "organization": ""}], "original": "By SAPNA MAHESHWARI and KATIE BENNER"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/26/business/media/making-video-ads-that-work-on-facebooks-silent-screen.html", "lead_paragraph": "Marketers trying to reach an increasingly fractured and fickle social media audience are struggling to make ads when one version may not work everywhere.", "headline": {"main": "Making Video Ads That Work on Facebook\u2019s Silent Screen", "content_kicker": "Advertising", "print_headline": "No Sound Needed: Producing Video Ads for Facebook\u2019s Silent Screen"}, "_id": "57e85ea795d0e021d79884a0", "word_count": "1349", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2016/09/26/business/media/26adco-geicocombo/26adco-geicocombo-thumbWide.png", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2016/09/26/business/media/26adco-geicocombo/26adco-geicocombo-thumbWide.png", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 600, "url": "images/2016/09/26/business/media/26adco-geicocombo/26adco-geicocombo-ar